headline: US homebuilder Lennar's quarterly revenue beats estimates on higher sales
summary: However, its average sales price of $389,000 declined from $408,000 in the first quarter and was lower than $426,000 a year earlier, as affordability for home buyers remains an issue. As a result, second quarter profit of $1.81 per share nearly halved from $3.45 a year earlier. Lennar delivered 20,131 homes during the quarter ended May 31, above 19,690 units a year earlier, and in line with its own forecast of 19,500 to 20,500 homes.
